<assessment id="u3_m0_intro5_lbd2_tutor2">
    <title>Tutor</title>
    <page>
        <question id="q1">
            <body><p> P(H) is <input_ref input="A"/>, therefore the coin is <input_ref input="B"/>. </p></body>
            
            <fill_in_the_blank id="A" shuffle="false">
                <choice value="res1">0.5</choice>
                <choice value="res2">not close to 0.5</choice>
            </fill_in_the_blank>
            
               <fill_in_the_blank id= "B" shuffle="false">
                <choice value="res1">fair</choice>
                <choice value="res2">not fair</choice>
               </fill_in_the_blank>            
            
            <part>
                <response input="A" match="res1" name="0.5" score="0">
                    <feedback>Incorrect. Recall that in the previous question we
                        determined that P(H) was 0.2.</feedback>
                </response>
                <response input="A" match="res2" name="is not close to 0.5" score="1">
                    <feedback>Correct. Since P(H) was about0.2, it is not close to 0.5.</feedback>
                </response>
            </part>
            <part>
                <response input="B" match="res1"  name="fair" score="0">
                    <feedback>Incorrect. Since P(H) ≠ 0.5 or even close to 0.5, the
                        possible outcomes (heads, tails) are not equally likely. In our case, P(H) =
                        0.2, so P(T) = 0.8. Thus, the coin is not fair.</feedback>
                </response>
                <response input="B" match="res2"  name="not fair" score="1">
                    <feedback>Correct. Since P(H) ≠ 0.5 or even close to 0.5, the possible outcomes
                        (heads, tails) are not equally likely. In our case P(H) = 0.2, so P(T) =
                        0.8. Thus, the coin is not fair.</feedback>
                </response>
   
            </part>
        </question>
        
        
        
